hopEase — E-Commerce Website (SEC035 Experiment 7)
Course: Web Programming with Python and JavaScript Lab (SEC035)
Program: B.Tech CSE | Semester II | Session 2025-26 (Even)
Department: SOET | Faculty: Mr. Aryan Sharma

Project Structure
ecommerce_website/
├── index.html      ← Full single-page app (hero, products, cart, checkout)
├── style.css       ← All CSS — layout, cards, cart, checkout, animations
├── script.js       ← All JavaScript — products, cart logic, checkout, filters
└── README.md       ← This file
How to Run
# Option 1 — Just open in browser (no server needed)
Double-click index.html

# Option 2 — Using Python simple server (recommended)
cd ecommerce_website
python -m http.server 8000
# Then open: http://localhost:8000
Features & Tasks
Task	Feature	Details
Task 1	Project setup & homepage	Hero section with stats, shapes, floating cards
Task 2	Product listing	12 products in responsive card grid, emoji placeholders
Task 3	CSS Styling	Warm luxury theme — teal + gold, DM Sans + Playfair Display
Task 4	Cart functionality	Add/remove items, dynamic rendering
Task 5	Price calculation	Subtotal, shipping (free above ₹999), total — all live
Task 6	Checkout simulation	Full form (name, address, payment), order confirmation modal
Task 7 ✨	Bonus features	Qty +/- buttons, localStorage persistence, category filter, sort, toast alerts
JavaScript Features (script.js)
Product data array — 12 items across 5 categories
Category filter pills (Electronics, Fashion, Accessories, Home, Sports)
Sort by price (low/high) or name
Add to Cart — highlights button when added
Quantity controls (+ / −) per cart item
Remove individual item or clear entire cart
Real-time price calculation (subtotal + conditional shipping + total)
Free shipping above ₹999 with discount row display
Checkout form with client-side validation + shake animation
Order confirmation modal with order ID, customer details, total
Cart state saved in localStorage — survives page refresh
Toast notifications for all actions
References
Google Fonts (DM Sans, Playfair Display): https://fonts.google.com/
